│ # 1.6.5.2. Level set methods                                                 │
│                                                                              │
│ Level set methods are popular in the CFD community be- cause of their        │
│ simplicity and speed. They were originally de- veloped by Osher and his      │
│ students, and their books [SET 99, OSH 02] are highly recommended.           │
│                                                                              │
│ A level set function is deﬁned for the interface between each pair of        │
│ contacting materials. It is usually the signed dis- tance function, d(x),    │
│                                                                              │
│ $$                                                                           │
│ d (\boldsymbol {x}) = \boldsymbol {n} \cdot d (\boldsymbol {x}),             │
